I"±<p>Iâ€™ve been an Assistant Professor at <a href="http://www.cmi.ac.in">Chennai Mathematical Institute</a> since May 2016.
I received my PhD in October 2013 from <a href="http://math.rutgers.edu">Rutgers University</a> under the supervision of <a href="http://math.rutgers.edu/~asbuch">Anders Buch</a>. I am primarily interested in Schubert calculus and algebraic combinatorics.
In particular, I study the K-theory, equivariant cohomology, and quantum cohomology of Grassmannians and their generalizations.</p>

